BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:0CbacK1A6LPc2VmFz-oGa
SUMMARY:Audubon Bird Walk
DTSTAMP:20260318T234503Z
DTSTART:20260319T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:Learn more about the birds at the Bellevue Botanical Garden. Jo
	in Eastside Audubon for a monthly walk that explores the birds and their h
	abitat in the Garden. This one-mile walk will be on trails with various su
	rfaces and may include gravel\, mulch\, or pavement. Please dress for the 
	weather and wear comfortable walking shoes. Parking in the lot is free. Fr
	om the parking lot enter the garden through the breezeway and turn left. M
	eet your guide in the covered Gathering Place. This walk is for any level 
	of birder and no experience is necessary. Bring binoculars if you have the
	m. There will be some available to loan for the walk. Each walk is $5 per 
	person. Registration is required.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#
	/details/audubon-bird-walk/15998889/2026-03-19T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/audubon-bird-walk/1599888
	9/2026-03-19T00
LOCATION:Bellevue Botanical Garden\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:P_ANcR8UBlqPdmUqPnvLH
SUMMARY:Figure/Ground: New Criteria
DTSTAMP:20260318T234503Z
DTSTART:20260319T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Figure/Ground: New Criteria is inspired by cultural historian S
	arah Lewis’s concept of “groundwork aesthetics\,” exploring figure-ground 
	relationships and their connection to social tension. It builds on Lewis’s
	 work\, which—set against the expansion of Stand Your Ground laws across t
	he United States since 2005\, laws that broadly define rights to use letha
	l self-defense against perceived threats—describes a range of artistic int
	erventions that reimagine “the literal and figurative meaning of ground.” 
	Primarily featuring works from the Henry collection created in the twenty-
	first century\, Figure/Ground reflects a period in which hard-won civil ri
	ghts and claims to self-determination have been eroded across the US\, dis
	proportionately affecting Black\, Brown\, LGBTQ\\+\, and other marginalize
	d communities.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/figure-gro
	und-new-criteria/17923441/2026-03-19T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/figure-ground-new-criteri
	a/17923441/2026-03-19T00
LOCATION:Henry Art Gallery\, 15th Ave NE & 41st St\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT9H
END:VEVENT
