UID:CB6VrvCDfV31U4o6gInmS
SUMMARY:Squak Mountain Celebration Hike
DTSTAMP:20260318T234504Z
DTSTART:20260325T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join IATC Vice President Selena Eon for an afternoon hike on Sq
	uak Mountain to celebrate all of the hard work volunteer crews have put in
	 to restore these trails in the wake of the 2024 bomb cyclone. Throughout 
	2025\, over 130 IATC volunteers worked to remove debris and restore tread 
	to trails on Squak over the course of 25 work parties.  We’ll meet at Moun
	tainside Drive Trailhead \\(also known as Bullitt Fireplace Trailhead\\) a
	nd work our way up to Old Griz\, where a substantial portion of the 2025 t
	rail work took place. We’ll also view the landslide sites on Phil’s Creek 
	before heading down the Eastside Trail back to the trailhead. Trails: Moun
	tainside Drive Trail\, Old Griz\, Phil’s Creek\, Eastside Trail Meeting Lo
	cation: Mountainside Drive Trailhead Date & Time: Wednesday\, March 25th\,
	 12:00 PM - 5:00 PM Duration: 5 hours Distance: 5 miles Elevation Gain: 13
	00 feet NOTE: This hike includes 1300 feet of elevation gain over 5 miles\
	, making it a moderate to difficult hike.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/
	events/#/details/squak-mountain-celebration-hike/18270843/2026-03-25T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/squak-mountain-celebratio
	n-hike/18270843/2026-03-25T00
